WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:47.101 --> 00:49.092
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

00:49.501 --> 00:51.378
[WOMAN CACKLING]

00:51.541 --> 00:53.179
FRED:
Come on.

00:57.101 --> 00:58.853
Split up.

01:02.421 --> 01:04.980
SHAGGY: Hey, come on, Scoob.
SCOOBY: I'm right behind you, Shaggy.

01:05.141 --> 01:07.132
[SHAGGY SCREAMS]

01:07.661 --> 01:09.731
Change of plans.

01:13.421 --> 01:15.412
WOMAN:
Stay out.

01:15.581 --> 01:17.572
[GRUNTING]

01:18.501 --> 01:21.538
Time to unmask the person
behind this mystery.

01:23.021 --> 01:25.694
- It's you?
- What?

01:25.861 --> 01:28.614
Like, it can't be.

01:38.781 --> 01:41.818
MAN: Remember, people, just because
this is the last day of class...

01:42.021 --> 01:43.977
...doesn't mean
this test doesn't count.

01:47.781 --> 01:48.975
Huh?

01:52.621 --> 01:54.293
No.

02:06.261 --> 02:07.376
Yes.

02:08.541 --> 02:10.610
Cowabunga.

02:14.941 --> 02:16.340
- Hot dog.
- Hot dog.

02:17.781 --> 02:19.658
GIRL 1:
Let's dance.

02:21.661 --> 02:23.413
Yeah.

02:35.341 --> 02:36.376
[GIRL 2 WHISTLES]

02:37.021 --> 02:40.491
Uh, guys, what are you doing?

02:40.701 --> 02:42.896
I know you're excited
the school year's over...

02:43.061 --> 02:45.017
...but our seasonal employment
awaits.

02:45.221 --> 02:48.497
Already? Like, I didn't even have time
to get a tan.

02:48.661 --> 02:50.333
- Yeah.
- Come on.

02:55.181 --> 02:57.172
[CHEERING]

03:00.941 --> 03:03.580
Well, it sure is lucky
that Daphne's uncle...

03:03.741 --> 03:06.255
...is opening his new country club
this summer, hey, V?

03:06.421 --> 03:09.413
Indeed. Without these summer jobs,
we'd never able to pay back...

03:09.581 --> 03:12.049
...Old Man Frickert
for the damage we did to his barn.

03:12.581 --> 03:14.537
Say cheese.

03:14.701 --> 03:15.975
[GIGGLES]

03:16.141 --> 03:18.735
- What is he...?
- Oh, Scoob's got a new hobby.

03:18.901 --> 03:20.300
Scrapbooking.

03:20.461 --> 03:23.578
- What happened to gardening?
- It didn't work out.

03:23.741 --> 03:26.778
Everything he planted,
he'd just dig right up.

03:28.181 --> 03:29.580
VELMA:
Hm.

03:29.981 --> 03:33.610
Daphne said we should hit the road
right after school.

03:33.781 --> 03:35.897
Any sign of her or Fred?

03:36.061 --> 03:37.540
Uh-uh.

03:38.581 --> 03:39.775
[VELMA GASPS]

03:39.941 --> 03:42.011
- Like, huh?
VELMA: Jinkies.

03:42.221 --> 03:43.620
Ooh.

03:44.341 --> 03:46.013
Perfect.

03:48.701 --> 03:52.216
Well? I for one think we deserve
an explanation.

03:52.381 --> 03:54.019
- Yeah.
- Yes.

03:54.221 --> 03:58.692
There's always been an undeniable
chemistry between you two, but...

03:58.861 --> 04:02.410
When did the transformative reaction
finally occur?

04:03.421 --> 04:05.810
I guess it started that night
at Old Man Frickert's.

04:05.981 --> 04:07.778
Yeah. Remember, Velma?

04:07.941 --> 04:11.411
<i>We followed the trail of the vengeful</i>
<i>scarecrow up into the hayloft.</i>

04:11.581 --> 04:13.412
This is impossible.

04:13.581 --> 04:16.015
We'll never find anything in here.

04:16.380 --> 04:18.940
Yes, if I wasn't so pun averse...

04:19.101 --> 04:22.137
...I might even say it's like looking
for a needle in a haystack.

04:22.301 --> 04:23.495
[MAN ROARS]

04:23.661 --> 04:25.492
MAN:
Didn't scare you, did I?

04:25.701 --> 04:27.100
[VELMA & DAPHNE SCREAMING]

04:27.261 --> 04:28.660
Daphne.

04:31.221 --> 04:32.813
Are you okay?

04:33.581 --> 04:35.458
I am now.

04:37.261 --> 04:39.456
SHAGGY: Like, run!
- What is it, Shaggy?

04:39.621 --> 04:42.818
- This one's gonna be a real barn burner.
FRED: Shaggy.

04:43.381 --> 04:45.053
Look out!

04:47.501 --> 04:50.061
DAPHNE: And thus,
we're stuck paying for a new barn.

04:50.221 --> 04:52.291
Again, just for the record...

04:52.461 --> 04:54.929
...nowhere on those bales of hay
did it say flammable.

04:55.101 --> 04:57.569
SCOOBY: Yeah.
- Anyway, that was also the night...

04:57.741 --> 05:00.733
...that Fred and I realized
we were just meant to be.

05:04.021 --> 05:06.012
It's a lovely story.

05:06.181 --> 05:09.014
But I do feel obligated
to raise one concern.

05:09.181 --> 05:11.251
Whenever there's a shift
in a relationship...

05:11.421 --> 05:14.015
...between two individuals
within a group...

05:14.181 --> 05:17.730
...it inevitably has repercussions
on the group as a whole.

05:18.981 --> 05:21.700
SHAGGY:
Oh, Velma, don't worry about that.

05:21.861 --> 05:24.580
We're all way too mature
to let that happen.

05:24.741 --> 05:27.619
- Right, Scoob?
- I know I am.

05:29.061 --> 05:30.460
Punch buggy white.

05:30.621 --> 05:33.931
Ouch. Oh, good one, Scoob.

05:34.101 --> 05:37.332
But it's a shame you didn't notice
the punch buggy green.

05:37.501 --> 05:38.854
Ow!

05:40.701 --> 05:42.259
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY GRUNTING]

05:42.421 --> 05:44.810
- All right.
- You know what? That is it. I've had it.

05:44.981 --> 05:48.257
You know, I will turn this van around.

05:49.621 --> 05:51.691
- Do I have to come back there?
DAPHNE: Scooby-Doo...

05:51.861 --> 05:54.136
...get your tail out of my face.

05:55.341 --> 05:58.014
DAPHNE: Fred, where are those
directions I sent you to print out?

05:58.221 --> 06:01.850
Don't worry, we're not lost.

06:07.221 --> 06:10.611
DAPHNE: Hm. This sure doesn't look
like my uncle's country club.

06:11.701 --> 06:14.454
Oh. Hey, look. It's the <i>S.S. Daphne.</i>

06:15.461 --> 06:17.292
DAPHNE:
Ha, ha.

06:17.461 --> 06:19.895
Oh, look. Try stopping there, sweetie.

06:20.101 --> 06:22.217
FRED:
Whatever you say, dear.

06:30.701 --> 06:32.931
VELMA:
Oh, how quaint.

06:42.541 --> 06:43.530
Hm.

06:43.701 --> 06:45.612
Hello?

06:45.821 --> 06:47.937
Anybody home?

06:48.141 --> 06:51.292
Like, yikes. Maybe we ought to just find
our own way...

06:51.461 --> 06:53.497
...to your uncle's country club.

06:54.701 --> 06:55.690
Zoinks!

06:55.861 --> 06:57.010
Country club?

06:57.181 --> 07:00.139
You're going to the country club?

07:00.301 --> 07:02.132
Yes, we have summer jobs there.

07:02.341 --> 07:06.459
No, you must turn back.
You must leave while you still can.

07:06.621 --> 07:10.455
- Leave? Why would we wanna leave?
- They were fools to build there.

07:10.621 --> 07:11.736
I tried to warn them...

07:11.901 --> 07:14.210
...but they thought
I was just some crazy hag.

07:14.381 --> 07:16.576
You? Heh. No.

07:16.781 --> 07:20.820
But mark my words,
the lake monster will return.

07:21.021 --> 07:24.855
The lake monster will return.

07:25.821 --> 07:27.812
[WHIMPERING]

07:28.501 --> 07:30.492
- Did you get directions?
- Uh...

07:30.661 --> 07:32.492
- Not exactly.
SHAGGY: Oh, yes, we did.

07:32.701 --> 07:35.659
Make a U-turn
and head straight back to Coolsville.

07:35.861 --> 07:39.137
There's a monster at the lake, guys.
A monster.

07:39.341 --> 07:41.411
- A monster?
- Mm-hm.

07:41.621 --> 07:44.579
Would you be referring
to the lake monster of Erie Pointe?

07:45.141 --> 07:47.496
You know, I didn't catch his name.

07:47.661 --> 07:50.653
- All I heard was "monster."
VELMA: No, look.

07:52.341 --> 07:55.777
It says here for hundreds of years
there have been sightings...

07:55.941 --> 07:59.570
...of hideous creatures
said to live at the bottom of the lake.

07:59.781 --> 08:03.296
I get it, it's one of those things
like Bigfoot or the Loch Ness monster.

08:03.501 --> 08:06.493
Oh, no, it's worse than we thought.

08:06.661 --> 08:09.653
No, Shaggy, I think what Fred means
is that it's just a legend.

08:09.821 --> 08:13.052
You know, lots of small towns
make them up. They're good for tourism.

08:13.501 --> 08:16.538
Oh. Oh, sure, you know,
come for the scenery...

08:16.701 --> 08:19.010
...stay for the certain death.

08:19.621 --> 08:20.610
[THUD]

08:20.781 --> 08:23.341
Come on, guys. Let's just get going
or we're gonna be late.

08:25.421 --> 08:27.093
Uh, Fred?

08:27.741 --> 08:30.858
- We still don't know how to get there.
- Mm-hm.

08:31.021 --> 08:35.139
Actually, yes, we do.

08:35.461 --> 08:36.655
[SHAGGY SIGHS]

08:36.821 --> 08:38.220
- No.
- Yes.

08:50.021 --> 08:51.454
FRED:
Pretty swank, Daph.

08:51.621 --> 08:55.455
DAPHNE: Yeah, looks like my uncle
really outdid himself this time.

08:59.301 --> 09:01.019
Thanks, Shaggy.

09:01.541 --> 09:02.530
[LAUGHS]

09:02.701 --> 09:06.535
- Is that my favorite niece?
- Uncle Thorny.

09:08.141 --> 09:09.369
Wow.

09:10.741 --> 09:12.697
Thank you again, uncle.

09:12.861 --> 09:15.659
I don't know what we would've done
without these summer jobs.

09:15.821 --> 09:18.619
Yeah. And, again, just for the record...

09:18.781 --> 09:21.614
...it's a well-known fact
that scarecrows are afraid of fire...

09:21.781 --> 09:22.770
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

09:22.941 --> 09:25.853
Gang, I'd like you to meet
Thorton Blake IV.

09:26.021 --> 09:27.340
Fifth, actually.

09:27.501 --> 09:29.173
Uncle Thorny, this is the gang.

09:29.381 --> 09:30.370
This is Shaggy.

09:30.541 --> 09:31.656
- Hi.
- Hi.

09:31.821 --> 09:33.413
- Fred.
- Oh.

09:33.861 --> 09:35.214
DAPHNE: Velma.
- Pleasure.

09:35.381 --> 09:36.734
- And...
SCOOBY: Scooby-Doo.

09:36.901 --> 09:38.414
Nice to meet you, Uncle Thorny.

09:38.581 --> 09:40.378
Smile.

09:40.541 --> 09:42.133
[SCOOBY GIGGLES]

09:42.821 --> 09:45.938
Well, I'm sure glad to have you all
on board this summer.

09:46.141 --> 09:50.373
Grab your stuff, get settled,
and park that thing in the back.

09:50.541 --> 09:53.578
Oh. You're gonna need
to get a good night's sleep.

09:53.741 --> 09:57.256
Your shifts start at 6 a.m. sharp.

09:58.461 --> 10:00.099
There's a 6 a. m?

10:01.101 --> 10:02.090
[SIGHS]

10:03.861 --> 10:06.580
And that one. It's my makeup.

10:09.621 --> 10:11.293
[SHAGGY GRUNTING]

10:11.461 --> 10:14.737
- Shaggy, need a hand?
- No, thanks, Fred. I got it.

10:14.901 --> 10:17.495
It just takes a little elbow grease.

10:17.661 --> 10:19.140
[GASPING]

10:19.301 --> 10:20.529
Shaggy.

10:23.421 --> 10:27.494
Shaggy, are you all right?

10:28.181 --> 10:30.536
Like, I am now.

10:31.421 --> 10:32.649
Shaggy.

10:33.381 --> 10:35.099
Yes, Velma?

10:35.301 --> 10:39.135
I don't know how much longer
I can hold you.

10:50.421 --> 10:52.377
- Hey, Scoob?
- Huh?

10:53.701 --> 10:56.374
- Can I talk to you man-to-man?
- Uh...

10:56.541 --> 10:58.497
Sort of.

10:58.701 --> 11:01.932
I think I might have just had
a hayloft moment with Velma.

11:03.101 --> 11:05.410
Do you think it's possible that...?

11:05.581 --> 11:11.213
I don't know,
that she and I are meant to be?

11:12.021 --> 11:14.057
[LAUGHING]

11:17.261 --> 11:19.855
Yeah. Thanks for the support, pal.

11:20.061 --> 11:22.655
I'll remember this come flea season.

11:24.981 --> 11:26.972
[PUFFING]

11:29.901 --> 11:31.892
[CONTINUES LAUGHING]

11:37.301 --> 11:38.700
[TREE BRANCHES RUSTLE]

11:39.501 --> 11:42.493
Getting much better distance
on those woods, sir.

11:43.181 --> 11:48.016
Hey, Fred,
can I talk to you man-to-man?

11:48.661 --> 11:50.253
Sort of.

11:50.821 --> 11:55.178
Well, you and Daphne,
is that something you recommend?

11:55.341 --> 11:56.899
What do you mean?

11:57.061 --> 11:59.529
Well, you know, going from having...

11:59.701 --> 12:03.216
...you know, a girl friend
to a girlfriend.

12:03.381 --> 12:07.454
Heh, heh. I don't know if I'd really
call Daphne my girlfriend, Shags.

12:07.621 --> 12:10.055
You know, it's more casual than that.
We're just, um...

12:10.221 --> 12:12.451
- We're hanging out.
- Hanging out?

12:12.621 --> 12:15.260
No, Fred is totally my boyfriend.

12:15.421 --> 12:16.649
Really?

12:16.821 --> 12:19.779
I always thought football players
liked to, well...

12:19.941 --> 12:21.852
...play the field.
- Pfft.

12:22.021 --> 12:26.890
Me too. I never thought Fred would
be the relationship type, but he totally is.

12:27.101 --> 12:28.693
I'm just not the relationship type.

12:28.861 --> 12:31.978
I'm a football player,
we like to, uh, play the field.

12:32.141 --> 12:33.893
Anyhow, it's summer, Shaggy.

12:34.061 --> 12:36.814
Oh, yeah, summer. Totally.

12:37.541 --> 12:41.534
Because who'd want a girlfriend
during daylight-savings time?

12:42.581 --> 12:44.173
Good guess, but what I'm saying...

12:44.341 --> 12:47.378
...is summer's a time you just wanna
have fun. Not get so serious.

12:47.541 --> 12:49.771
Daphne's cool,
she feels the same way.

12:49.941 --> 12:52.057
It's totally getting serious.

12:52.221 --> 12:54.337
Fred's cool, he feels the same way.

12:54.501 --> 12:58.540
Well, it certainly sounds
like you two are perfectly in sync.

12:58.701 --> 12:59.736
Yeah.

12:59.901 --> 13:01.812
- Exactly.
- Exactly.

13:02.021 --> 13:04.012
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

13:05.261 --> 13:07.252
[YAWNS]

13:09.381 --> 13:10.575
SHAGGY:
Hey, Scoob.

13:10.781 --> 13:15.536
- How was the first dog day of summer?
- Relaxing.

13:15.741 --> 13:18.380
Glad to hear it, boy.
Now, come on, let's go get some...

13:18.541 --> 13:21.613
Oh, hello, Velma.

13:21.821 --> 13:24.858
- How was your day?
- Fine, I guess.

13:25.021 --> 13:28.172
Oh, really? Like, mine was fine too.

13:28.341 --> 13:30.775
It's crazy
how much we have in common, huh?

13:31.301 --> 13:32.370
Oh, boy.

13:32.541 --> 13:35.578
So, guys, my uncle invited us
to the opening night reception.

13:35.741 --> 13:37.811
- What do you say?
- Awesome.

13:37.981 --> 13:40.256
- How about a dip in the pool first?
DAPHNE: Sounds great.

13:42.501 --> 13:46.210
Oh, like, that sounds like a real rager.
What do you think, V?

13:46.421 --> 13:49.140
Perhaps I'll rendezvous
with everyone later.

13:49.341 --> 13:53.653
Since we arrived, I've been eager
to survey the indigenous flora and fauna.

13:54.421 --> 13:56.377
Oh, hey. Wait up.

13:56.541 --> 14:00.056
So you say there's both flora and fauna
out there, huh?

14:00.221 --> 14:03.975
When was the last time you heard
those two things in the same sentence?

14:05.341 --> 14:06.330
[BELCHES]

14:07.301 --> 14:11.214
Shaggy, did you know
Lake Erie is the warmest...

14:11.421 --> 14:14.652
...and most biologically productive
of the Great Lakes?

14:14.821 --> 14:18.291
Not to mention
the eleventh largest lake in the world.

14:18.461 --> 14:19.450
[METAL DETECTOR BEEPING]

14:19.621 --> 14:20.940
SHAGGY:
Oh, wow.

14:21.461 --> 14:24.737
I could listen to you talk like that
for hours.

14:25.781 --> 14:28.295
Are you really interested
in this stuff, Shaggy?

14:29.221 --> 14:34.090
I've never known you to be,
well, intellectually curious.

14:35.661 --> 14:38.050
Oh, I'm curious
about a lot of things, Velma.

14:38.261 --> 14:39.489
Like...

14:39.661 --> 14:42.129
Like people and relationships...

14:42.301 --> 14:45.657
...and relationships between people.

14:50.141 --> 14:51.938
Hey.

14:53.421 --> 14:55.013
[GRUNTING]

14:55.941 --> 14:59.490
Hey, Shaggy,
you're gonna love this factoid.

15:00.021 --> 15:03.696
Lake Erie has been gradually rising
over the last few hundred years.

15:03.901 --> 15:07.780
That means beneath
all of these rock formations...

15:07.941 --> 15:10.250
...there are miles
of underwater caves.

15:10.461 --> 15:12.975
- Get out of town.
- No, really.

15:13.141 --> 15:15.814
You can tell
by the variegated sedimentary striations.

15:16.421 --> 15:18.571
Oh, would you look at that.

15:18.741 --> 15:23.531
I've never seen irrigated rudimentary
claymations like that before.

15:24.581 --> 15:29.530
Hey, Velma, yesterday at the van...

15:29.861 --> 15:31.055
Uh...

15:31.221 --> 15:32.654
Jinkies.

15:33.181 --> 15:35.854
Look at this, Shaggy.

15:36.061 --> 15:38.939
I think it might actually
be a moonstone.

15:39.101 --> 15:40.739
They're very rare.

15:40.941 --> 15:42.852
You know,
the Native Americans believed...

15:43.021 --> 15:47.458
...they held this mystical connection
with the moon, thereby the name.

15:49.341 --> 15:51.650
Look at how it glows.

15:52.421 --> 15:54.935
It's beautiful, isn't it?

15:56.541 --> 15:58.418
It sure is.

15:58.581 --> 16:01.095
Almost as beautiful as your eyes.

16:02.581 --> 16:05.812
- Oh, Shaggy.
- Oh, Velma.

16:05.981 --> 16:08.973
Oh, Shaggy, I think I'm gonna be sick.

16:09.141 --> 16:13.339
- What? Oh, Velma, are you all right?
- I'm fine.

16:13.741 --> 16:15.936
I just feel really nauseous
all of a sudden.

16:16.141 --> 16:17.859
SHAGGY:
Like, you better sit down.

16:18.061 --> 16:19.972
- Here, let me help.
- No, it's okay.

16:20.341 --> 16:24.016
I'm just gonna go back to the room
and lie down for a little while.

16:25.261 --> 16:27.331
Oh, okay.

16:34.821 --> 16:37.051
I think she likes me.

16:37.301 --> 16:39.337
Oy vay.

16:42.141 --> 16:44.132
[PIANO PLAYING]

16:44.341 --> 16:47.219
THORNY: Well, I'll catch you out there
on the links, huh?

16:47.381 --> 16:48.575
Oh.

16:48.741 --> 16:52.017
Senator. I'm so glad
you could make it.

16:52.181 --> 16:57.050
Oh, how could I ever say no
to my biggest contributor?

16:57.221 --> 16:58.700
- How about a photograph?
- Yes.

17:02.541 --> 17:05.896
- Good thing I dressed up, hey, Scoob?
SCOOBY: Yeah.

17:06.060 --> 17:08.939
Hey, Shagg, Scoob. Where's Velma?

17:09.101 --> 17:10.454
Oh. Uh, heh.

17:10.621 --> 17:14.694
Uh, she got sick all of a sudden.
But it was totally natural causes...

17:14.861 --> 17:17.011
...and not revulsion
at the very thought of me.

17:17.941 --> 17:19.010
Okay.

17:22.501 --> 17:26.255
- Hey, Scoob, check out the buffet.
- Ooh.

17:27.181 --> 17:30.491
Now, if you don't mind,
one from my best side.

17:31.701 --> 17:32.895
One more.

17:37.581 --> 17:40.095
This will be good in my scrapbook.

17:41.181 --> 17:42.853
Perfect.

17:58.301 --> 18:00.656
Like, who ordered the pea soup?

18:08.981 --> 18:10.699
THORNY:
Sorry, everyone.

18:10.901 --> 18:14.177
I'm sure it's just a little minor glitch
with one of our generators.

18:14.341 --> 18:15.535
I'll just...

18:16.221 --> 18:17.210
[GROWLING]

18:17.381 --> 18:19.019
What the heck is that?

18:19.221 --> 18:21.212
[GASPING]

18:23.901 --> 18:26.369
- Fred?
- I don't know either, Daph.

18:31.981 --> 18:33.096
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

18:33.261 --> 18:34.694
[ROARING]

18:34.861 --> 18:38.012
SCOOBY:
Lake monster.

18:39.741 --> 18:43.017
Excuse me, I don't recall
having seen your name on the guest list.

18:53.781 --> 18:55.692
[SCREAMING]

19:01.301 --> 19:02.620
[PHOTOGRAPHER SCREAMS]

19:06.181 --> 19:08.331
That thing can't be real, can it?

19:08.501 --> 19:12.050
I don't know, but I'm not
getting close enough to find out.

19:13.061 --> 19:14.096
Hi.

19:16.701 --> 19:18.419
[ROARS]

19:24.861 --> 19:25.850
THORNY:
No, please.

19:26.021 --> 19:27.010
Please, everyone...

19:27.181 --> 19:30.173
...I'm sure there's a logical explanation
as to what's going on.

19:30.341 --> 19:31.740
We'll just tidy up the tent...

19:31.901 --> 19:35.018
...and, you know,
we'll just continue the party.

19:35.181 --> 19:36.660
Everyone... Oh, senator, senator.

19:36.821 --> 19:39.938
MAN: Give me the keys, I'll get it myself.
WOMAN: Just go without him.

19:40.421 --> 19:41.649
My goodness.

19:42.381 --> 19:45.930
Why do I have the feeling
I missed something rather significant?

19:46.101 --> 19:49.332
It was the lake monster.
The lake monster of Erie Pointe.

19:49.541 --> 19:53.773
It was horrifying, terrifying,
scariest thing I've ever seen in my life.

19:53.941 --> 19:57.138
On a more personal note,
how are you feeling, Velma?

19:57.301 --> 20:00.611
- Did you just say the lake monster?
- Yeah.

20:00.781 --> 20:01.816
You can't be serious.

20:01.981 --> 20:04.939
Oh, my guests sure seemed to think
it was serious.

20:05.101 --> 20:06.659
Look at this, not even day one...

20:06.821 --> 20:09.210
...and half of them
have canceled their memberships.

20:09.381 --> 20:12.339
If somebody doesn't figure out
what's going on here quickly...

20:12.501 --> 20:15.174
...it's gonna be a very short summer
for all of us.

20:16.221 --> 20:18.940
Guys, we have to do something.

20:19.101 --> 20:22.138
We can't afford to lose these jobs.

20:30.341 --> 20:31.330
Oh, no.

20:31.501 --> 20:32.775
No, no, no.

20:32.941 --> 20:34.897
- You guys thinking what I'm thinking?
- No.

20:35.061 --> 20:36.892
- Come on.
- Guys, please, don't...

20:37.261 --> 20:38.250
[SIGHS]

20:38.421 --> 20:40.218
Here we go again.

20:40.421 --> 20:42.139
Uncle Thorny.

20:43.501 --> 20:46.015
We just wanna let you know
not to worry.

20:46.181 --> 20:47.853
Not only did you hire summer help...

20:48.021 --> 20:52.060
...you also hired the best supernatural
detectives in the tristate area.

20:52.261 --> 20:54.252
- I did?
- That's right.

20:54.421 --> 20:56.537
And I know just where to start too.

20:56.701 --> 20:58.896
With Elmer Uggins,
the person who's taken...

20:59.061 --> 21:01.621
...the only known photo
of the lake monster.

21:16.301 --> 21:18.656
FRED:
Heh. Would you look at that.

21:18.821 --> 21:22.575
Our first suspect just happens to be
the keeper of a creepy old lighthouse.

21:22.781 --> 21:24.339
You know, just once...

21:24.501 --> 21:29.097
...I wish we found a mystery
that started in a cheery futon showroom.

21:29.781 --> 21:30.975
What?

21:31.141 --> 21:35.134
Futons offer far more support
than traditional mattresses.

21:41.061 --> 21:43.052
[FOGHORN BLOWS]

21:55.421 --> 21:58.379
Well, looks like the light's on
but nobody's home.

21:58.541 --> 22:01.613
Isn't this the part when we normally
split up and search for clues?

22:01.781 --> 22:03.692
I'll go with Velma. Ha.

22:05.221 --> 22:07.052
Come on. It'll be fun.

22:07.941 --> 22:10.978
Okay. Come on, Daph.

22:17.781 --> 22:19.373
[SHAGGY SNIFFING]

22:19.541 --> 22:24.171
Oh, Velma, what is that sweet fragrance
you're wearing?

22:24.621 --> 22:26.259
Bug and tick repellent.

22:26.421 --> 22:27.570
[MOSQUITO BUZZING]

22:27.741 --> 22:31.017
Well, it certainly isn't repelling me.

22:36.021 --> 22:37.420
[CLEARS THROAT]

22:38.861 --> 22:41.534
It sure is a lovely night, huh?

22:41.701 --> 22:44.534
I've always enjoyed
strolling beneath a full moon.

22:44.701 --> 22:47.693
Werewolves notwithstanding,
of course.

22:48.101 --> 22:51.980
I too enjoy walking
by the light of the silvery moon.

22:52.141 --> 22:53.210
[CHUCKLES]

22:53.381 --> 22:56.657
Heh, heh, heh.
Yeah, that's a good one.

22:56.821 --> 22:58.413
Wait, where's the funny?

22:59.061 --> 23:01.655
- Oh. "By the Light of the Silvery Moon"?
- Yeah.

23:01.821 --> 23:04.540
It's just an old vaudevillian ditty.

23:04.741 --> 23:08.336
But I must confess,
I do have a soft spot for it.

23:10.701 --> 23:14.899
Like, wait, I think I do know that one.

23:21.901 --> 23:24.415
- [SINGING] <i>By the light</i>
CHORUS: <i>Not the dark, but the light</i>

23:24.581 --> 23:27.732
- <i>Of the silvery moon</i>
CHORUS: <i>Not the sun, but the moon</i>

23:27.901 --> 23:30.973
- <i>I wanna spoon</i>
CHORUS: <i>Not broom, but spoon</i>

23:31.141 --> 23:35.532
<i>To my honey I'll croon love's tune</i>

23:35.701 --> 23:38.454
- <i>Honeymoon</i>
- <i>Honeymoon, honeymoon</i>

23:38.621 --> 23:41.419
- <i>Keep a-shining in June</i>
- <i>Keep a-shining in June</i>

23:41.581 --> 23:45.017
<i>Your silvery beams</i>
<i>Will bring love's dreams</i>

23:45.181 --> 23:47.934
<i>We'll be cuddling soon</i>

23:48.381 --> 23:51.976
<i>By the light of the silvery</i>

23:52.261 --> 23:56.254
CHORUS: <i>Moon</i>
SHAGGY: <i>Moon</i>

23:56.501 --> 23:58.492
[RECORD SCRATCHING]

23:58.741 --> 24:00.936
ALL [SINGING]:
<i>Act one, scene new</i>

24:01.101 --> 24:03.490
<i>Act two</i>
<i>Me, you</i>

24:03.661 --> 24:05.572
<i>Let's go</i>
<i>New tune</i>

24:05.741 --> 24:07.459
- <i>By the light</i>
- <i>Not the dark, but the light</i>

24:07.621 --> 24:10.135
- <i>Of the silvery moon</i>
- <i>Not the sun, but the moon</i>

24:10.301 --> 24:12.371
- <i>I wanna spoon</i>
- <i>Not broom, but spoon</i>

24:12.541 --> 24:15.214
- <i>To my honey I'll croon</i>
- <i>Croon! Five, six</i>

24:15.381 --> 24:17.337
- <i>By the moon</i>
- <i>By the moon, by the moon</i>

24:17.501 --> 24:19.651
- <i>Keep it shining in June</i>
- <i>Keep it shining in June</i>

24:19.821 --> 24:22.051
<i>Your silvery beams</i>
<i>Will bring love's dreams</i>

24:22.221 --> 24:24.576
- <i>We'll be cuddling soon</i>
- <i>We'll be cuddling soon</i>

24:24.741 --> 24:27.460
<i>By the silvery moon</i>

24:39.861 --> 24:44.059
Hey, Fred, you don't think Shaggy
could have a crush on Velma, do you?

24:44.221 --> 24:47.338
Not unless she turned into
a steaming bowl of chili cheese fries.

24:47.501 --> 24:48.900
[CHUCKLES]

24:50.061 --> 24:52.291
- Why?
- I don't know, it's just...

24:52.461 --> 24:54.656
...he's been acting really goofy lately.

24:54.821 --> 24:56.413
Even for Shaggy.

24:56.581 --> 24:59.573
And he's been following Velma around
like a puppy dog.

24:59.741 --> 25:02.255
Actually, that would explain
why he's been asking me...

25:02.421 --> 25:04.332
...all those questions about dating.

25:04.501 --> 25:07.095
But I guess he didn't take my advice.

25:07.261 --> 25:09.729
Advice? Wait, Fred, what advice?

25:14.461 --> 25:15.860
[CREATURE GROWLING]

25:16.701 --> 25:21.536
Um, Velma, that wasn't what I thought
it was, was it?

25:21.701 --> 25:22.929
I don't know.

25:23.101 --> 25:27.652
Did you surmise that it was a heretofore
unclassified amphibious humanoid?

25:28.141 --> 25:32.851
No. I thought it was a lake monster!
Zoinks!

25:33.021 --> 25:34.374
Fred?

25:34.541 --> 25:38.011
Exactly what advice
did you give Shaggy about dating?

25:38.181 --> 25:39.170
What?

25:39.341 --> 25:43.380
Oh, you know, just that it's summertime
and we're not really...

25:43.541 --> 25:44.576
[CREATURE ROARS]

25:44.741 --> 25:45.810
Come on.

25:46.021 --> 25:47.852
Go, go, go!

25:48.061 --> 25:50.734
SHAGGY:
It's the lake monster! Save me.

25:50.941 --> 25:53.136
MONSTER:
Ow! My ankle.

25:53.301 --> 25:54.814
What?

25:58.821 --> 25:59.856
UGGINS:
Hey.

26:00.421 --> 26:01.979
Mr. Uggins, I presume?

26:05.781 --> 26:07.339
Call me Elmer.

26:09.061 --> 26:10.335
Hi, kids.

26:12.781 --> 26:16.330
So you've never actually seen
the monster?

26:16.501 --> 26:19.573
I was just using the legend
to make a quick buck.

26:19.741 --> 26:21.891
Made some postcards...

26:22.101 --> 26:24.615
...sold them to the local tourist traps.

26:25.341 --> 26:26.490
- Mm?
- No.

26:26.661 --> 26:28.458
- No.
- Thanks.

26:29.141 --> 26:30.130
Hey, what can I say?

26:30.301 --> 26:32.940
You know, lighthouse keeping
ain't exactly a growth industry.

26:33.101 --> 26:34.580
[CHUCKLING]

26:35.221 --> 26:36.700
Ahem. Anyway...

26:36.861 --> 26:40.331
...when I heard about all the hoopla
down at the country club tonight...

26:40.501 --> 26:44.813
...I figured it might be a good time
to dust off old green-eyes over there...

26:45.021 --> 26:46.500
...and take some new shots.

26:46.661 --> 26:48.174
[IMITATING CAMERA SHUTTER
CLICKING]

26:48.341 --> 26:49.615
But listen, kids...

26:49.821 --> 26:53.211
...if this thing's really back,
you best leave now while you still can.

26:53.421 --> 26:56.299
Come on, you don't really believe
the monster's real, do you?

26:56.501 --> 26:58.856
It's probably some prankster
with a better costume.

26:59.021 --> 27:01.057
Maybe it is and maybe it ain't.

27:01.221 --> 27:03.212
But one thing's for sure...

27:03.381 --> 27:07.010
...the legend is a truly terrible tale.

27:07.181 --> 27:11.459
It all goes back
to the very beginnings of town.

27:11.661 --> 27:14.653
When the first settlers arrived
in these parts...

27:14.821 --> 27:17.494
<i>... they was confronted</i>
<i>by an old woman...</i>

27:17.661 --> 27:20.733
<i>... who was said to live</i>
<i>in a cave by the lake.</i>

27:20.941 --> 27:22.659
Grubwort was her name.

27:22.861 --> 27:24.738
<i>Wanda Grubwort.</i>

27:24.901 --> 27:27.620
<i>She claimed all the land around the lake</i>
<i>belonged to her...</i>

27:27.781 --> 27:30.739
...and told the settlers that
if they didn't turn back...

27:31.261 --> 27:33.297
...they would pay the price.

27:33.861 --> 27:37.217
But them early pioneers was not about
to be turned away so easily...

27:37.381 --> 27:43.058
...so they settled in
and forgot all about her warning.

27:43.421 --> 27:46.811
But Wanda Grubwort did not forget.

27:46.981 --> 27:52.055
And one day,
she fulfilled her dark oath.

27:53.501 --> 27:56.174
<i>Using her magical staff...</i>

27:56.381 --> 28:00.169
<i>... she cast a spell</i>
<i>upon an innocent creature of the lake...</i>

28:01.021 --> 28:05.060
...transforming it into a hideous beast.

28:09.661 --> 28:12.255
<i>Once Grubwort</i>
<i>had her monstrous slave...</i>

28:12.421 --> 28:15.094
<i>... she loosed it upon the villagers.</i>

28:21.741 --> 28:24.619
And then? What happened next?

28:24.781 --> 28:28.615
Well, it's said the settlers
eventually overcame Grubwort...

28:28.781 --> 28:33.332
...tried her for witchery
and burned her at the stake.

28:36.021 --> 28:37.613
Like I said...

28:38.981 --> 28:42.018
...you best leave now
while you still can.

28:43.501 --> 28:46.220
I'm sorry, Mr. Uggins,
but we just don't give up that easy.

28:47.021 --> 28:50.730
He obviously wasn't
in my sophomore geometry class.

28:52.221 --> 28:53.620
[UGGINS GRUNTS]

28:54.501 --> 28:58.574
SHAGGY:
Mr. Shaggy...

28:59.661 --> 29:01.652
...Dinkley.

29:01.861 --> 29:04.216
It's like the angels are singing it.

29:04.741 --> 29:07.130
- Mister...
- Hey, Shagg. What you doing?

29:08.221 --> 29:10.610
Oh! Um... Nothing.

29:17.381 --> 29:21.818
Doctor says I need more linen
in my diet.

29:22.821 --> 29:24.698
Okay. So, have you seen Fred?

29:25.781 --> 29:27.499
He's out on the...

29:27.701 --> 29:30.010
Out on the green,
putting with some girls.

29:30.821 --> 29:31.810
Girls?

29:31.981 --> 29:34.575
FRED:
Now, just remember to follow through.

29:35.061 --> 29:37.052
GIRL 1:
Follow through.

29:39.101 --> 29:40.853
Hey.

29:41.061 --> 29:43.131
GIRL 1: Thanks.
FRED: Okay, guys, I'm out of here.

29:43.861 --> 29:45.977
- Okay, I'll see you guys later.
- Bye.

29:46.141 --> 29:48.496
GIRL 2: Bye, Fred.
FRED: Bye now.

29:49.901 --> 29:51.220
Hey, Daph.

29:51.421 --> 29:53.013
- What's up, Shags?
- Hey, Fred.

29:56.381 --> 29:57.530
What?

29:57.701 --> 29:59.419
Hey, um...

30:00.181 --> 30:02.172
...can I ask your advice
about something?

30:02.341 --> 30:03.694
Sure.

30:03.901 --> 30:05.937
Well, I...

30:07.141 --> 30:09.052
See, I have this friend, okay?

30:09.221 --> 30:12.452
His name's, um, Scruffy. Yeah, Scruffy.
They call him that...

30:12.621 --> 30:15.693
...because he has a goatee.
No, that would be too obvious.

30:15.901 --> 30:21.055
Anyway, so this friend of mine,
who doesn't have a goatee or a dog...

30:21.261 --> 30:23.217
...definitely doesn't have
a dog either...

30:23.421 --> 30:26.777
...he has this crush on this girl
he sometimes solves mysteries with.

30:26.981 --> 30:29.017
No, no. That's a dead giveaway.

30:29.581 --> 30:31.731
- Let me start over. So...
- Shaggy.

30:32.421 --> 30:35.140
It's okay. We know you like Velma.

30:36.061 --> 30:37.050
[SCOFFS]

30:37.221 --> 30:38.449
Oh. Oh, what?

30:38.621 --> 30:40.851
Oh, I don't know
what you guys are talking about.

30:41.021 --> 30:43.296
I definitely do not like... Velma.

30:43.461 --> 30:46.771
You are not gonna believe what I found
in the security footage. Come on.

30:49.861 --> 30:54.059
After you watch this,
I think you'll all be saying "jinkies."

30:55.341 --> 30:58.094
Hey, the security camera
caught the attack.

30:58.301 --> 31:01.452
Yep. And they caught
something else too.

31:05.301 --> 31:08.338
Looks like we have two pranksters
on our hands.

31:08.541 --> 31:09.894
Jinkies.

31:10.861 --> 31:13.056
- Told you.
- Freeze it.

31:13.221 --> 31:16.099
If you zoom in right here,
we can see who's inside that cloak.

31:21.621 --> 31:23.851
SHAGGY:
Oh, look, it's coming into focus.

31:24.701 --> 31:26.293
[SHAGGY SCREAMS]

31:27.181 --> 31:28.614
What happened?

31:28.781 --> 31:31.534
Like, that spooky figure
must be using some sort of magic...

31:31.701 --> 31:33.771
...to prevent us from seeing its face.

31:33.941 --> 31:39.095
I'm afraid the explanation is slightly
less supernatural than that, Shaggy.

31:39.301 --> 31:43.977
I accidentally knocked over my green tea
and short-circuited the hard drive.

31:44.461 --> 31:46.179
- Oh.
- That's okay, Velma.

31:46.381 --> 31:49.578
You know, I'm sure we'll find
another piece of critical evidence.

31:49.741 --> 31:51.140
- Right, guys?
- Yeah, for sure.

31:51.301 --> 31:52.575
- It's groovy.
FRED: Don't worry.

31:52.781 --> 31:55.579
I know this is highly
uncharacteristic behavior.

31:56.981 --> 31:59.256
I'm really sorry, guys.

32:03.901 --> 32:06.415
I'll tender my resignation from the group
if you wish.

32:06.581 --> 32:07.570
- What?
- What?

32:07.741 --> 32:08.730
DAPHNE: Velma.
- Come on.

32:08.901 --> 32:10.459
Velma.

32:13.021 --> 32:14.374
Like, hold on, V.

32:17.741 --> 32:21.939
Don't beat yourself up about this.
You just pulled a Shaggy, that's all.

32:22.661 --> 32:24.299
I do it all the time.

32:25.421 --> 32:28.572
Thanks, Shaggy,
but there's really no excuse.

32:29.541 --> 32:33.500
Maybe reading a little Sylvia Plath
will buoy my spirits.

32:34.421 --> 32:35.774
Hey, I...

32:35.941 --> 32:38.136
I still think you're wonderful.

32:38.301 --> 32:41.259
Shaggy, that was so nice.

32:41.461 --> 32:44.897
That's exactly how you should be
if you're really serious about Velma.

32:45.261 --> 32:47.217
Oh. Oh, what?

32:47.381 --> 32:49.212
Oh, what do you mean?

32:49.381 --> 32:50.814
I do not...

32:52.101 --> 32:53.693
All right, I admit it.

32:53.861 --> 32:55.214
I like Velma.

32:55.381 --> 32:58.453
I'm my friend. I'm Scruffy.

32:59.981 --> 33:01.778
But what am I gonna do?

33:01.941 --> 33:04.455
You know, I don't know
what I'm supposed to say to her.

33:04.621 --> 33:06.498
Let me help you out, Shags.

33:06.701 --> 33:08.339
You gotta be confident, smooth.

33:08.541 --> 33:10.338
- Girls like guys...
- Don't listen to him.

33:10.501 --> 33:12.492
He has no idea what girls like.

33:12.661 --> 33:15.129
See, what girls like is to feel special.

33:15.301 --> 33:17.576
To feel like they're the only one
on a guy's mind.

33:17.741 --> 33:20.016
Yeah, I know that.
But listen, what you wanna do...

33:20.181 --> 33:22.934
Well, if you know that,
then why don't you try it sometime?

33:23.141 --> 33:25.052
What's with you?
Why are you acting weird?

33:25.221 --> 33:27.974
- How exactly am I act...?
- Like, you know what?

33:28.181 --> 33:30.012
Forget I even asked.

33:30.221 --> 33:32.177
I'll just figure this out for myself.

33:32.341 --> 33:36.129
Besides, if I ever get Velma to like me,
I want it to be real...

33:36.301 --> 33:38.735
...not some loosey-goosey thing
like you guys have.

33:43.021 --> 33:45.171
Fred, did you say something
to Shaggy...

33:45.341 --> 33:48.492
...about us having
a "loosey-goosey" relationship?

33:48.701 --> 33:50.692
What? Oh, no, no.

33:51.421 --> 33:53.173
I just told him how we're casual.

33:53.341 --> 33:56.697
You know, how it's summer
and we're just hanging out.

33:57.461 --> 34:00.692
I mean,
that is what we're doing, right?

34:00.861 --> 34:04.774
Yes, Fred.
That is exactly what we're doing.

34:04.941 --> 34:10.572
I'm just so glad
that we're on the same page.

34:13.221 --> 34:17.100
Well, she's not the president
of the drama club for nothing.

34:18.141 --> 34:19.699
I like you, Velma Dinkley.

34:19.900 --> 34:21.300
So, what do you say?

34:21.501 --> 34:24.572
- Will you go on a date with me?
- Sorry, not my type.

34:24.741 --> 34:26.333
Like, come on, Scoob.

34:26.541 --> 34:28.850
Forget Velma.

34:29.661 --> 34:32.539
Time for a midnight snack.

34:32.981 --> 34:35.097
SHAGGY: A what?
- A midnight snack.

34:35.261 --> 34:39.697
You know, a couple of sandwiches,
a rack of ribs, pepperoni?

34:39.860 --> 34:43.614
- What?
- Oh, just follow me. Whew.

34:44.301 --> 34:45.370
Just my luck.

34:45.541 --> 34:49.011
I've got a talking dog
and I can't understand a word he says.

35:06.701 --> 35:08.692
SHAGGY:
Mm, mm, mm.

35:08.941 --> 35:11.774
Sandwich, look out.

35:13.501 --> 35:15.412
[SNIFFS THEN SIGHS]

35:15.581 --> 35:17.219
Is that Eau de' Dinkley I detect?

35:19.181 --> 35:20.330
Shaggy?

35:20.501 --> 35:24.938
Shaggy? Hey, what about
my midnight snack?

35:25.101 --> 35:27.092
[GROWLS]

35:28.621 --> 35:29.849
Huh.

35:30.261 --> 35:31.933
DAPHNE:
Nice shot.

35:43.741 --> 35:45.379
Mine.

35:45.581 --> 35:47.014
[MAN GRUNTS
AND DAPHNE SHRIEKS]

35:59.781 --> 36:01.737
Velma?

36:04.621 --> 36:06.737
Where is she?

36:13.461 --> 36:14.450
[TWIG CRACKS]

36:14.621 --> 36:16.020
[SIGHS]

36:19.861 --> 36:22.295
Oh, Velma, is that you?

36:25.581 --> 36:26.570
[ROARS]

36:26.941 --> 36:28.090
[SCREAMS]

36:31.381 --> 36:32.370
Oh, hi, Fred.

36:34.181 --> 36:35.455
Is something wrong?

36:35.661 --> 36:37.333
SHAGGY:
Help!

36:37.501 --> 36:39.696
- Help, help!
- Come on.

36:40.701 --> 36:41.929
- Shaggy.
- Aah!

36:42.101 --> 36:43.693
- What's wrong?
- Oh.

36:43.861 --> 36:45.453
Oh, you know, nothing.

36:45.621 --> 36:48.010
I just thought I'd work
on my blood-curdling scream.

36:48.181 --> 36:50.900
What the heck do you think is wrong?
It's the lake monster.

36:51.381 --> 36:52.370
Whoa!

36:54.101 --> 36:57.218
That's it, time to unmask this prankster
once and for all.

36:57.421 --> 36:59.412
[GRUNTING]

37:00.221 --> 37:02.735
Come on, help me with this mask.

37:06.141 --> 37:08.416
Fred, I don't think this thing
is a mask.

37:12.021 --> 37:14.774
Ew! Gross.

37:15.301 --> 37:17.178
FRED:
Keep moving.

37:19.421 --> 37:21.491
This thing keeps getting
the jump on us.

37:21.661 --> 37:24.619
It can't jump in two directions.
Come on, split up.

37:29.781 --> 37:31.339
Like, why did he have to pick me?

37:31.501 --> 37:34.334
In gym class,
I'm always the last one picked.

37:35.021 --> 37:36.010
Huh. Heh.

37:36.181 --> 37:37.773
Oh, zoinks.

37:37.941 --> 37:40.057
[ROARING]

37:43.981 --> 37:45.892
SCOOBY:
I'll save you, Shaggy.

37:49.381 --> 37:50.416
SHAGGY:
Like, thanks, buddy.

37:50.581 --> 37:53.175
I thought that giant mutant frog
was gonna make me croak.

37:53.381 --> 37:54.370
[SHAGGY GIGGLES]

37:54.541 --> 37:57.374
Oh, boy, I wish I could enjoy that one.

37:59.261 --> 38:01.695
Oh, heh. Oh. You did it, boy.

38:02.261 --> 38:03.455
Oh, what a friend.

38:03.621 --> 38:04.974
What a pal.

38:05.141 --> 38:06.176
What a sand trap.

38:06.581 --> 38:08.572
[BOTH SCREAMING]

38:14.581 --> 38:17.937
Oh, boy, Scoob.
I owe you one, buddy.

38:18.101 --> 38:20.615
If it wasn't for you, I would...

38:20.821 --> 38:23.381
Hey, would you look at that?

38:26.261 --> 38:28.377
- It's one of those moonstones.
- Yeah.

38:28.541 --> 38:31.977
Velma loves these things almost
as much I love deep-fried...

38:32.141 --> 38:33.859
Well, anything. Huh.

38:34.061 --> 38:35.733
Groovy.

38:36.021 --> 38:37.693
Huh? Hmph.

38:37.861 --> 38:40.659
Velma, Velma, Velma. Pfft.

38:43.581 --> 38:46.254
Hey, come on,
I think the coast is clear.

38:47.101 --> 38:50.093
This doesn't make sense.
There's no such thing as a lake monster.

38:50.261 --> 38:53.697
Tell that to the thing
that just threw up an aquarium.

38:53.981 --> 38:56.814
So now do you wanna tell me
who those guys were?

38:56.981 --> 38:58.300
Not now, Fred.

39:00.141 --> 39:02.132
[MONSTER GROWLING]

39:06.941 --> 39:09.660
Oh, that was worse than my date
with Herbie Zimmer.

39:09.861 --> 39:12.534
Totally, I... Wait, you went on a date
with Herbie Zi...?

39:13.541 --> 39:15.532
[MONSTER SCREAMING]

39:27.461 --> 39:28.655
WOMAN:
Creature.

39:29.421 --> 39:32.458
What are you doing?
You're supposed to be searching.

39:32.621 --> 39:34.612
With all the bedlam
you've raised tonight...

39:34.781 --> 39:36.499
...we'll have to stop early.

39:36.661 --> 39:38.014
Return to the lake.

39:38.181 --> 39:41.651
I'll summon you
when it's safe to resume our search.

39:51.061 --> 39:52.289
[DAPHNE SIGHS]

39:52.821 --> 39:55.096
- That was close.
- Yeah.

39:56.901 --> 39:59.540
Hey. Not bad.

39:59.741 --> 40:01.140
[SIGHS]

40:01.981 --> 40:03.937
Uncle Thorny.

40:04.741 --> 40:06.015
That thing came back.

40:06.181 --> 40:08.376
Oh, you think?

40:10.141 --> 40:13.372
Canceled memberships
and now all this damage.

40:14.101 --> 40:17.696
I hate to say it, I may have no choice
but to shut this place down...

40:17.861 --> 40:21.297
...and go back to my life
as an international playboy.

40:24.221 --> 40:25.290
SHAGGY:
Hey, guys.

40:25.501 --> 40:26.934
Shaggy, you're okay.

40:27.101 --> 40:30.616
Well, yeah, I am,
but has anyone seen Velma?

40:30.781 --> 40:33.818
Before the monster attacked,
she was out here, I know it.

40:33.981 --> 40:35.050
Oh, no.

40:35.221 --> 40:37.781
Oh, you don't think the lake monster
got to her, do you?

40:37.941 --> 40:40.614
I've seen monster movies,
I know how this works.

40:40.781 --> 40:42.453
[ROARS THEN SCREAMS]

40:42.621 --> 40:45.499
Shaggy, Shaggy. Calm down, okay?

40:45.661 --> 40:46.935
- We're gonna find her.
- Yeah.

40:47.101 --> 40:48.090
- Let's go.
SHAGGY: Okay.

40:48.261 --> 40:50.695
FRED:
Velma!

40:52.381 --> 40:54.133
DAPHNE:
Velma!

40:54.301 --> 40:55.814
Velma?

40:55.981 --> 40:56.970
Where are you?

40:57.141 --> 40:59.894
- Velma!
- Velma!

41:01.701 --> 41:04.340
Hey, guys, I found her.

41:09.341 --> 41:12.492
- Oh, no. She's dead.
- Oh!

41:12.661 --> 41:15.129
Oh, she looks so peaceful.

41:15.301 --> 41:17.690
Oh, I can't look.

41:18.101 --> 41:19.170
[GROANS]

41:19.661 --> 41:21.970
Uh... Guys?

41:24.621 --> 41:27.374
- What's going on?
- Oh, it's a miracle.

41:27.541 --> 41:30.055
FRED: What happened to you
last night, Velma?

41:30.461 --> 41:32.019
I don't know.

41:32.901 --> 41:36.371
I couldn't sleep,
so I went for a walk by the lake.

41:36.821 --> 41:38.937
But then that fog rolled in and...

41:40.141 --> 41:43.292
Well, I must have gotten lost.

41:43.461 --> 41:45.929
I sat down to wait until it lifted...

41:46.141 --> 41:48.291
...and I must have fallen asleep.

41:48.741 --> 41:51.050
Don't you ever do that to us again,
you hear?

41:51.221 --> 41:54.054
You had us all worried so...
What are those?

41:56.781 --> 41:59.534
- They kind of look like warts.
- Warts?

41:59.701 --> 42:01.214
Egads.

42:01.381 --> 42:03.178
Oh, no.

42:03.341 --> 42:08.938
I'm sure it's just some kind
of urushiol-induced dermatitis.

42:09.101 --> 42:11.012
- Oh.
- Yeah.

42:12.101 --> 42:15.093
Anyway, what's going on?

42:15.261 --> 42:18.333
You missed another attack.
Come on, we'll get you cleaned up...

42:18.501 --> 42:21.140
...and we'll fill you in.
VELMA: Another attack?

42:21.301 --> 42:23.974
Anybody else hungry? I know I am.

42:24.141 --> 42:25.210
Shocking.

42:25.421 --> 42:26.820
Mm.

42:27.501 --> 42:28.490
Ooh.

42:28.661 --> 42:31.380
So you think the monster's real
and someone's using it...

42:31.541 --> 42:32.974
...to dig up something
on the grounds?

42:33.141 --> 42:36.292
Yeah. Problem is, we don't have
a single clue about who's using it.

42:36.501 --> 42:41.416
Yes, we do. The mysterious figure
had a streak of purple paint on its cloak.

42:42.741 --> 42:45.539
- So?
- So remember the boat that we passed...

42:45.701 --> 42:48.852
...on the way up here?
Shaggy called it the <i>S.S. Daphne.</i>

42:49.021 --> 42:51.216
It was being painted
the exact same color.

42:51.421 --> 42:55.699
I'd be willing to bet that whoever's
behind this has been on that boat.

42:55.901 --> 42:57.892
All right, gang,
we know what we have to do.

42:58.341 --> 43:01.777
After our shifts tonight, we'll head
to the docks and we'll check it out.

43:03.941 --> 43:04.930
No.

43:07.501 --> 43:09.059
No.

43:09.501 --> 43:12.015
I'm not going
until I do what I've been trying to do...

43:12.181 --> 43:14.092
...since we first got here.

43:16.701 --> 43:21.217
Um, Velma, I learned something today.

43:21.381 --> 43:23.815
Life is like a chocolate soufflé.

43:24.501 --> 43:28.619
And if you wait too long to dig in,
it could just collapse on you.

43:29.261 --> 43:33.254
So anyway,
what I'm trying to say is...

43:37.621 --> 43:41.091
...Velma Dinkley,
will you go on a date with me?

43:42.141 --> 43:44.575
- Heh. A date?
- Yeah.

43:45.581 --> 43:47.333
Shaggy.

43:48.541 --> 43:50.133
Are you serious?

43:50.301 --> 43:53.976
I've never been more serious
about anything in my entire life.

43:54.181 --> 43:57.696
Except maybe dinosaurs,
but that was a long time ago.

43:58.861 --> 44:02.649
Shaggy, that's very sweet of you...

44:03.541 --> 44:06.931
...but we're right in the middle
of an investigation.

44:07.821 --> 44:10.733
Well, like,
I think Fred and Daphne can handle it.

44:10.941 --> 44:14.411
They probably wanna spend some
quality time together anyway, right?

44:14.581 --> 44:16.173
- No, not really.
- I'm good.

44:17.221 --> 44:19.496
I don't know, Shaggy.

44:19.661 --> 44:20.696
SHAGGY:
Oh.

44:22.021 --> 44:24.376
Like... Like, yeah, that's...

44:24.541 --> 44:25.769
I mean, that's fine.

44:25.981 --> 44:27.255
I...

44:27.821 --> 44:30.381
If I were you, I probably
wouldn't wanna go on a date...

44:30.541 --> 44:32.736
...with a goofy guy
like me either so...

44:37.941 --> 44:39.738
Hold on.

44:40.421 --> 44:42.173
Shaggy, you know what?

44:42.861 --> 44:45.216
I will go on a date with you tonight.

44:45.781 --> 44:46.770
Oh, really?

44:48.141 --> 44:49.972
- You mean it?
- Sure.

44:50.141 --> 44:51.130
Why not?

44:51.341 --> 44:53.377
Yes.

44:53.901 --> 44:55.414
Pick you up around 7.

44:57.061 --> 44:58.460
[GRUNTS]

44:59.021 --> 45:00.056
Seven o'clock.

45:03.621 --> 45:05.054
Slippery.

45:05.901 --> 45:06.890
[PIANO CRASHES]

45:07.061 --> 45:08.574
- Ouch.
SHAGGY: I'm okay.

45:11.941 --> 45:14.011
Oh, curse this mop top.

45:14.181 --> 45:16.741
I can't do anything with it.

45:19.141 --> 45:21.496
Okay, Scoob, how do I look?

45:21.661 --> 45:23.731
Ah. Handsome as a devil.

45:23.901 --> 45:26.290
What about me?

45:26.701 --> 45:28.054
Oh. Um...

45:28.221 --> 45:30.177
Like, as dapper as a Dalmatian...

45:30.341 --> 45:34.698
...but where are you headed, buddy?
- With you. Where else?

45:34.901 --> 45:38.371
Oh, um, heh. Um...

45:38.581 --> 45:41.049
You know, buddy...

45:41.221 --> 45:44.816
...I'm gonna have to fly solo
on this one tonight.

45:44.981 --> 45:47.620
- Solo?
- Yeah, you know, like...

45:47.781 --> 45:50.978
...you're just gonna have to do
your own thing, you know what I mean?

45:51.141 --> 45:54.929
My own thing? But, Shaggy...

45:55.101 --> 45:58.138
Thanks for understanding, Scoob.

45:58.981 --> 46:00.255
[SIGHS]

46:00.421 --> 46:02.218
I'll see you later, pal.

46:02.381 --> 46:05.054
Goodbye, Shaggy.

46:05.221 --> 46:07.212
[CRYING]

46:17.661 --> 46:19.538
[SHAGGY WHIMPERING]

46:19.701 --> 46:23.011
Who's the best puppy
in the whole wide world?

46:24.501 --> 46:26.492
[CONTINUES WHIMPERING]

46:28.181 --> 46:31.935
No. No more rolling over.

46:44.861 --> 46:45.976
- Ready?
- Yeah.

46:46.141 --> 46:48.257
Good. So...

46:48.421 --> 46:49.979
...who were they?

46:50.141 --> 46:51.813
Who were who?

46:52.621 --> 46:53.656
Oh, ho.

46:53.821 --> 46:57.530
Are you still wondering about those boys
I was playing tennis with?

46:57.701 --> 47:00.295
They were nobody, Fred.
Just some caddies I met.

47:00.461 --> 47:01.860
Why?

47:02.341 --> 47:03.774
You're not jealous, are you?

47:03.941 --> 47:06.171
Jealous? No, no.

47:06.341 --> 47:08.093
I'm not jealous. No way.

47:08.261 --> 47:10.252
I don't get jealous.

47:10.421 --> 47:12.173
Yeah, right.

47:26.181 --> 47:27.580
[SNIFFING]

47:31.621 --> 47:34.089
- Good evening, Norville.
- Heh.

47:34.541 --> 47:35.940
[CHUCKLES]

47:36.581 --> 47:38.173
Shaggy.

47:39.021 --> 47:40.693
Aren't you gonna say anything?

47:43.821 --> 47:46.893
I like corn dogs.

47:53.661 --> 47:56.016
- Thanks, Shaggy.
- Yeah.

47:59.501 --> 48:01.014
Thank you.

48:01.821 --> 48:03.777
Oh. Ahem.

48:15.821 --> 48:17.015
[CLEARS THROAT]

48:19.021 --> 48:21.819
Well, it looks like we got
the whole place to ourselves.

48:22.021 --> 48:27.015
Yes, unfortunately, that only emphasizes
the urgency of our investigation.

48:27.221 --> 48:29.815
- Sure we shouldn't check with Fred...?
- Oh, come on, V.

48:29.981 --> 48:33.451
Like, just try to put those frontal lobes
on the back burner tonight, okay?

48:34.741 --> 48:36.413
Okay, Shaggy.

48:36.581 --> 48:40.335
I must admit, I do have a hard time
letting myself relax.

48:40.541 --> 48:42.418
Especially recently.

48:42.621 --> 48:46.136
Ever since we've been here,
I just haven't felt like myself.

48:48.541 --> 48:51.419
Well, whoever you are, I like it.

48:53.341 --> 48:54.490
Thanks, Shaggy.

48:56.701 --> 48:57.975
Oh. Um...

48:58.141 --> 49:02.214
Now, come on,
I want this night to be perfect.

49:03.021 --> 49:04.420
[SCREAMS]

49:05.501 --> 49:06.536
Velma.

49:07.821 --> 49:09.539
VELMA:
My glasses.

49:09.701 --> 49:10.975
Here, let me help you up.

49:11.141 --> 49:12.210
Are you okay?

49:12.381 --> 49:13.734
I'm sorry, I...

49:13.901 --> 49:16.415
I don't know what came over me.

49:17.101 --> 49:18.739
Oh, here. Here you go.

49:18.901 --> 49:20.095
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

49:23.701 --> 49:26.773
Oh, boy.
Here, let me get you some water.

49:26.981 --> 49:30.451
<i>Garçon,</i> water, please.

49:30.941 --> 49:32.897
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

49:33.101 --> 49:34.090
[LAUGHING]

49:35.021 --> 49:36.818
[HUMMING]

49:41.661 --> 49:42.650
[SCOOBY BELCHES]

49:42.821 --> 49:44.015
[SCOOBY SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

49:44.861 --> 49:48.217
Oh, whoops.
I seem to have dropped my fork.

49:48.941 --> 49:51.501
Here, help me find it, waiter.

49:52.661 --> 49:54.299
Scooby-Doo, what are you doing?

49:54.461 --> 49:57.453
Waiting tables. Fresh ground pepper?

49:57.621 --> 50:00.419
Scooby, get out of here, buddy.
You're gonna ruin everything.

50:00.581 --> 50:02.253
No.

50:02.741 --> 50:07.019
Okay, but would you do it
for a Scooby snack?

50:07.181 --> 50:09.900
I can't be bought. Hmph.

50:10.741 --> 50:11.890
Now, you listen, Scoob...

50:12.061 --> 50:14.939
...I'm the master and I command you
to go back to your room...

50:15.101 --> 50:18.059
...and quit being such a bad dog.

50:19.901 --> 50:21.254
Puppy loving...

50:21.461 --> 50:23.452
[SCOOBY MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

50:24.421 --> 50:26.218
Bad dog? Huh.

50:26.421 --> 50:28.616
I'll show you a bad dog.

50:28.901 --> 50:31.017
[LAUGHS THEN GROWLS]

50:31.421 --> 50:33.377
No, Shaggy, don't.
The waiter will bring...

50:33.541 --> 50:34.815
[SCREAMS]

50:36.101 --> 50:37.773
Would you care to hear our specials?

50:37.941 --> 50:40.011
Scooby-Doo? Is that you?

50:40.221 --> 50:41.973
I didn't invite him.

50:42.181 --> 50:45.218
He just showed up
and tried to sabotage everything and...

50:45.381 --> 50:47.611
- And...
- Is that what I think it is?

50:49.821 --> 50:51.015
Oh, uh, heh.

50:51.181 --> 50:54.537
Yeah, that was supposed to be
a surprise.

50:54.741 --> 50:56.811
I found it in a sand trap last night.

50:57.021 --> 50:59.660
It's one of those moonstones, right?

51:00.221 --> 51:01.210
Yes.

51:01.421 --> 51:05.255
I was gonna give it to you when I walked
you back to your room tonight, but...

51:05.421 --> 51:07.491
It's beautiful.

51:09.541 --> 51:12.055
Excuse me, I have to go now.

51:12.701 --> 51:15.659
Wait, what? Well, Velma...

51:18.141 --> 51:19.893
This is all your fault, Scooby-Doo.

51:20.061 --> 51:21.858
You ruined everything.

51:22.021 --> 51:24.535
No, I didn't.

51:24.701 --> 51:26.100
[SCOOBY GROWLS]

51:35.021 --> 51:37.535
DAPHNE:
There it is, the purple boat.

51:37.701 --> 51:39.771
FRED:
She. There she is.

51:39.981 --> 51:41.334
A boat is a she, like a girl.

51:41.501 --> 51:43.571
But not one who goes around
playing tennis...

51:43.741 --> 51:46.096
...with every boy boat in the harbor.

51:55.741 --> 51:58.016
That cloaked figure
was definitely here.

51:58.181 --> 52:00.251
All hands on deck.

52:21.221 --> 52:23.781
Fred, look.

52:34.101 --> 52:36.137
- Ladies first.
- Mm-mm.

52:36.301 --> 52:37.734
Fine.

53:18.461 --> 53:20.895
Looks like a bunch of old newspapers.

53:21.061 --> 53:22.255
DAPHNE:
I'll say.

53:22.501 --> 53:23.900
FRED:
Huh.

53:25.181 --> 53:29.891
Hey, these are about that witch
from Uggins' story, Wanda Grubwort.

53:30.061 --> 53:32.859
DAPHNE: Evil staff?
- Yeah, remember? Didn't Elmer say...

53:33.021 --> 53:35.899
...an ancient staff was the source
of her black magic?

53:37.981 --> 53:39.573
DAPHNE:
Hey, look at this one.

53:41.541 --> 53:45.659
That must be what the monster's doing,
looking for the source of her powers.

53:45.821 --> 53:48.893
The problem is we still don't know
who's controlling it.

53:49.821 --> 53:52.415
Wait a second, maybe we do.

53:54.381 --> 53:57.930
Wanda Grubwort had children. She could
still have descendants living in town.

53:58.101 --> 53:59.295
Maybe one got angry...

53:59.461 --> 54:02.498
...when your uncle built on their land
and decided to get revenge.

54:05.141 --> 54:06.859
What was that?

54:09.501 --> 54:11.731
It's locked. Hello!

54:11.941 --> 54:13.579
Help. Help.

54:13.741 --> 54:17.177
DAPHNE:
Anyone out there? Let us out.

54:19.501 --> 54:20.536
Help. Help.

54:20.701 --> 54:22.896
Is anyone out there? Oh, great.

54:23.061 --> 54:25.291
If we don't get this open,
we'll be stuck here all night.

54:25.461 --> 54:26.894
[RUMBLING]

54:27.941 --> 54:29.693
That might be the least
of our worries.

54:30.581 --> 54:31.900
- Hello!
- Is anyone out there?

54:32.061 --> 54:33.050
Help!

54:33.901 --> 54:36.096
- Help, help!
DAPHNE: We need to get out.

54:36.261 --> 54:37.899
FRED: Help, anybody.
DAPHNE: Anyone!

54:38.101 --> 54:40.774
FRED: Help, anybody!
- Help, get us out!

54:40.941 --> 54:43.136
FRED:
Help, help, anybody!

54:43.341 --> 54:46.651
- Help, help.
- We're stuck, it's filling.

54:47.461 --> 54:50.055
Fred, you need to do something.
We're gonna drown.

54:50.261 --> 54:54.049
I have an idea. Why don't we call
those guys you were playing tennis with?

54:54.221 --> 54:57.816
- I knew it, you are jealous.
- Yeah, maybe I am.

54:57.981 --> 55:01.212
- Good, that was the point.
- You were just lying to make me jealous?

55:01.381 --> 55:04.691
Yes, I'm trying to pay you back
for playing golf with those floozies.

55:04.861 --> 55:06.977
Flooz...? Oh, that was different.

55:07.141 --> 55:09.097
How? How was that any different?

55:09.261 --> 55:11.491
I don't know, they were... It just was.

55:11.661 --> 55:13.253
All right, you know what, Fred?

55:13.421 --> 55:16.618
If I'm gonna die,
I don't want to die dating a jerk.

55:16.781 --> 55:20.296
Yeah, well, if I'm gonna die,
I don't want to die dating a sneaky...

55:20.941 --> 55:23.660
...manipulative, game-playing...

55:28.981 --> 55:31.290
You see that? I saved us.

55:31.461 --> 55:34.771
That's lovely,
but we're still broken up.

55:34.941 --> 55:35.930
What?

55:36.141 --> 55:37.779
Good.

55:38.461 --> 55:40.452
[MUTTERING]

56:02.581 --> 56:04.299
Like, what happened to you guys?

56:04.501 --> 56:05.775
What happened?

56:05.941 --> 56:07.533
We broke up, that's what happened.

56:07.741 --> 56:09.857
Yeah, best decision I ever made too.

56:10.061 --> 56:12.450
Did you just say best decision
you ever made?

56:12.621 --> 56:15.055
That's funny,
because I broke up with you.

56:15.221 --> 56:16.210
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

56:16.381 --> 56:18.019
What? You did not.

56:18.181 --> 56:19.819
- Guys?
DAPHNE: I did so.

56:19.981 --> 56:21.573
Guys.

56:21.781 --> 56:26.901
That's a real bummer and all,
but I kind of meant, why are you wet?

56:27.221 --> 56:28.654
Oh, that.

56:28.821 --> 56:31.699
Well, let's just say we almost got in
over our heads.

56:31.861 --> 56:34.819
But we figured out
that Wanda Grubwort's descendant...

56:34.981 --> 56:38.610
...might be trying to reconstruct
her magical staff.

56:41.461 --> 56:44.897
Hey, how'd it go with Velma?

56:46.221 --> 56:49.372
Yeah. Ask my waiter.

56:49.581 --> 56:51.856
DAPHNE:
Grubek, Grubel, Guzzak.

56:52.621 --> 56:53.610
No Grubwort.

56:54.261 --> 56:58.857
Huh. Would you look at that.
What a crazy coincidence.

56:59.861 --> 57:01.817
What's that, Shags?

57:02.261 --> 57:06.174
Oh. Remember that creepy general store
we stopped at on the way in?

57:06.701 --> 57:08.737
It was called Trowburgs.

57:08.901 --> 57:13.258
Well, if you spell Trowburg backwards
you get Grubwort.

57:13.461 --> 57:14.735
What are the odds, huh?

57:14.901 --> 57:18.291
Excuse me,
you are on my side of the room.

57:27.701 --> 57:29.100
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY GULP]

57:41.461 --> 57:42.689
[THUNDER CRASHING]

57:44.421 --> 57:46.298
There. Shaggy, Scooby,
go around back.

57:46.461 --> 57:48.691
- I'm not going with him.
- I'm not going with him.

57:48.861 --> 57:51.216
- You think I want to go with you?
SHAGGY: Seriously...

57:51.381 --> 57:53.053
SCOOBY: I'm not going with Shaggy.
FRED: Enough.

57:53.221 --> 57:55.291
- Guys, let's just go.
- Go.

57:59.141 --> 58:00.813
- Surprise.
WOMAN: Oh, no.

58:00.981 --> 58:02.334
[WOMAN CACKLING]

58:02.501 --> 58:04.093
Come on.

58:04.781 --> 58:06.180
Hey, wait for me.

58:15.941 --> 58:17.579
In here.

58:25.301 --> 58:27.019
SCOOBY:
This way.

58:27.741 --> 58:29.333
The other way.

58:34.221 --> 58:35.620
[SHAGGY SCREAMING]

58:38.661 --> 58:39.650
No.

58:41.341 --> 58:43.855
FRED: Come on.
SHAGGY: No, please.

58:44.021 --> 58:45.500
Please.

58:51.981 --> 58:54.051
- Now can we split up?
- Ugh.

58:58.901 --> 59:01.369
SHAGGY: Hey, come on, Scoob.
- I'm right behind you, Shaggy.

59:01.541 --> 59:03.532
[SHAGGY SCREAMS]

59:04.061 --> 59:06.177
Change of plans.

59:09.501 --> 59:12.299
WOMAN:
And stay out.

59:14.981 --> 59:18.018
Time to unmask
the person behind this mystery.

59:19.661 --> 59:22.255
- It's you?
- What?

59:22.421 --> 59:24.537
Like, it can't be.

59:26.781 --> 59:27.975
Velma?

59:28.901 --> 59:32.098
[IN DISTORTED VOICE]
Oh, you fools. I'm not Velma.

59:33.101 --> 59:34.454
[DAPHNE SCREAMS]

59:34.621 --> 59:36.418
Daphne.

59:37.861 --> 59:39.852
I don't want to hurt you, Velma.

59:40.061 --> 59:42.621
Oh, but I do want to hurt you,
pretty boy.

59:44.101 --> 59:45.534
Sorry, Velma.

59:45.701 --> 59:47.817
[GRUNTING]

59:52.861 --> 59:56.490
Velma. What's going on?
Why are you doing this?

59:56.701 --> 59:58.373
Our date wasn't that bad, was it?

59:58.581 --> 01:00:03.814
Why? To make them pay,
to make them all pay.

01:00:03.981 --> 01:00:08.736
Now, that I've rebuilt my staff,
no one can stop me.

01:00:16.541 --> 01:00:17.940
[COUGHING]

01:00:25.981 --> 01:00:30.657
Well, there's another mystery solved,
huh, gang?

01:00:31.221 --> 01:00:32.449
I got it.

01:00:32.621 --> 01:00:34.213
Okay.

01:00:35.421 --> 01:00:39.460
What in the world is going on?
Why is Velma doing this?

01:00:39.941 --> 01:00:41.169
Oh, no.

01:00:41.381 --> 01:00:44.134
You don't think my passions
drove her mad, do you?

01:00:44.301 --> 01:00:46.690
I'm sure there's something bigger
than that going on.

01:00:46.861 --> 01:00:48.089
I'll say.

01:00:49.101 --> 01:00:53.617
Your friend has been possessed by
the spirit of the witch Wanda Grubwort.

01:00:54.261 --> 01:00:58.812
Oh, great, my first love
and she's turned into an evil witch.

01:00:58.981 --> 01:01:00.972
Join the club.

01:01:09.061 --> 01:01:11.495
Yeah. Hee, hee, hee.

01:01:11.661 --> 01:01:12.776
It was that staff.

01:01:12.941 --> 01:01:14.260
[IMITATES EXPLOSION]

01:01:14.421 --> 01:01:16.696
She must have found the pieces...

01:01:16.861 --> 01:01:20.490
...that have been buried
all these many years.

01:01:21.101 --> 01:01:23.535
Like, by any chance...

01:01:23.701 --> 01:01:26.340
...did moonstones
play any part in this?

01:01:26.901 --> 01:01:30.416
As soon as your friend touched one
of those rocks...

01:01:30.581 --> 01:01:33.812
...the spirit of my evil ancestor
took hold of her...

01:01:33.981 --> 01:01:37.257
...and compelled her to find the rest.

01:01:37.421 --> 01:01:39.889
SCOOBY: For you, old lady.
- Oh.

01:01:41.101 --> 01:01:44.411
So it's been Velma the entire time?

01:01:44.621 --> 01:01:48.250
Like, zoinks.
It's been right under our noses.

01:01:48.461 --> 01:01:50.850
<i>The evil spirit must have first taken</i>
<i>hold of her...</i>

01:01:51.021 --> 01:01:53.012
<i>... when we found that stone</i>
<i>by the lake.</i>

01:01:53.781 --> 01:01:57.820
And those creepy warts, it was like
she was actually turning into a witch.

01:01:58.021 --> 01:01:59.374
Being burned at the stake...

01:01:59.541 --> 01:02:02.339
<i>... would make me pretty freaked out</i>
<i>at the sight of fire too.</i>

01:02:02.541 --> 01:02:05.419
And I bet she intentionally shorted out
the security console...

01:02:05.581 --> 01:02:07.890
<i>... because she knew</i>
<i>we'd see her face.</i>

01:02:08.461 --> 01:02:10.417
I can't believe we missed it.

01:02:10.581 --> 01:02:13.459
I guess we were all too wrapped up
in our own little dramas...

01:02:13.621 --> 01:02:15.976
...to catch the really big one going on.

01:02:16.781 --> 01:02:17.770
[SIGHS]

01:02:18.261 --> 01:02:23.460
So now that she has her powers back,
what's Wanda Grubwort going to do?

01:02:23.621 --> 01:02:26.931
I fear that what she seeks
is the revenge...

01:02:27.101 --> 01:02:30.377
...that has eluded her all these years.

01:02:31.101 --> 01:02:32.853
Who cares about what she wants.

01:02:33.021 --> 01:02:36.900
We gotta save Velma. Do you have
any idea where she would have gone?

01:02:37.101 --> 01:02:39.695
Oh, probably to the caves
where she lived.

01:02:39.861 --> 01:02:41.055
The caves?

01:02:41.261 --> 01:02:43.855
But what about the irrigated
rudimentary claymations?

01:02:44.061 --> 01:02:45.050
The what?

01:02:45.221 --> 01:02:48.258
The entrances to the caves,
they're all underwater.

01:02:48.421 --> 01:02:49.740
How would we get in?

01:02:50.661 --> 01:02:52.970
You're in luck. I rent scuba gear.

01:02:53.181 --> 01:02:55.775
I'll give you a good deal too.

01:03:07.821 --> 01:03:09.732
Smile.

01:03:50.701 --> 01:03:52.817
Zoinks.

01:04:04.901 --> 01:04:06.698
FRED:
Lights.

01:04:24.741 --> 01:04:25.730
Uh-oh.

01:04:33.141 --> 01:04:34.733
VELMA [IN DISTORTED VOICE]:
Ah.

01:04:34.901 --> 01:04:37.813
You've been a faithful servant.

01:04:37.981 --> 01:04:42.736
And now I think you deserve
some playmates.

01:04:42.901 --> 01:04:44.459
[BELLOWS]

01:04:46.461 --> 01:04:48.497
She's making more of those things.

01:04:55.421 --> 01:04:57.810
VELMA:
Rise, my slithering slaves.

01:04:58.021 --> 01:05:01.377
Rise and serve your new master.

01:05:06.261 --> 01:05:08.252
[GROWLING]

01:05:08.621 --> 01:05:09.610
[GASPS]

01:05:09.781 --> 01:05:11.976
Finally, we'll make them pay.

01:05:12.141 --> 01:05:15.497
Make them rue the day
they set foot on our land.

01:05:16.141 --> 01:05:18.575
Those things are gonna attack
everyone in town.

01:05:18.741 --> 01:05:21.733
- We have to do something.
- What can we do?

01:05:21.901 --> 01:05:25.371
Hey, Fred, I know this is usually
your department, but do you mind...?

01:05:25.541 --> 01:05:28.294
- If you've got a plan, Shaggy, go for it.
- Okay.

01:05:29.581 --> 01:05:33.130
Velma Dacey Dinkley,
you stop that this instant.

01:05:34.181 --> 01:05:39.778
I told you,
Velma doesn't live here anymore.

01:05:39.981 --> 01:05:42.336
That was your big idea, Shags?

01:05:42.541 --> 01:05:45.738
Creatures, change of plans.

01:05:45.941 --> 01:05:47.135
Get them.

01:05:48.421 --> 01:05:50.332
SCOOBY:
Hold still.

01:05:53.621 --> 01:05:55.179
Thank you. Aah!

01:06:05.981 --> 01:06:06.970
Velma.

01:06:07.141 --> 01:06:10.736
Velma, I know you're still in there.
I know you can hear me.

01:06:12.661 --> 01:06:15.459
Okay, like, maybe you can't.

01:06:19.941 --> 01:06:21.294
DAPHNE:
This is like biology class...

01:06:21.461 --> 01:06:24.498
...except this time
the frogs are gonna dissect us.

01:06:26.341 --> 01:06:28.491
Like, come on, V.
You gotta listen to me.

01:06:28.661 --> 01:06:31.414
You're stronger than this thing
inside of you.

01:06:31.621 --> 01:06:35.819
You're stronger
and you're smarter and you're cuter.

01:06:36.661 --> 01:06:39.300
- [IN NORMAL VOICE] I am?
- That's right, V.

01:06:39.461 --> 01:06:42.976
I think everything about you is cute.
Like the way...

01:06:43.141 --> 01:06:45.780
...your pleated skirt ruffles
when you run from ghosts.

01:06:45.981 --> 01:06:47.300
How... And even...

01:06:47.461 --> 01:06:51.454
Even how you lose your glasses
at the most inopportune moments.

01:06:51.621 --> 01:06:56.615
Yeah. Yeah, as a matter of fact,
that might be the cutest thing of all.

01:06:57.501 --> 01:06:59.332
Shaggy?

01:06:59.981 --> 01:07:02.256
- Help me.
- Yeah.

01:07:02.461 --> 01:07:05.373
Yeah, listen, V.
You gotta fight this old witch.

01:07:05.581 --> 01:07:06.570
- Okay.
- Okay?

01:07:06.741 --> 01:07:09.539
Shaggy, I'll try. I'll try.

01:07:09.701 --> 01:07:11.498
[IN DISTORTED VOICE]
No, you won't.

01:07:12.581 --> 01:07:14.333
[SHAGGY SCREAMING]

01:07:18.381 --> 01:07:22.818
Well, at least now I can finally say
I've been picked up by a girl.

01:07:43.461 --> 01:07:45.656
See you, froggies.

01:07:54.101 --> 01:07:56.171
FRED:
Run, run.

01:08:05.461 --> 01:08:07.816
That ought to hold them for a while.
Come on.

01:08:12.781 --> 01:08:15.136
Knock me down all you want,
Wanda Grubwort...

01:08:15.341 --> 01:08:19.732
...but I'm not gonna let a couple of
stupid moonstones take my friend away.

01:08:20.701 --> 01:08:22.930
Oh, wait, moon. Oh, that's it.

01:08:23.861 --> 01:08:26.898
[SINGING]
<i>By the light of the silvery moon</i>

01:08:27.060 --> 01:08:28.176
What is it? What are you...?

01:08:28.341 --> 01:08:30.138
<i>By the light</i>

01:08:30.301 --> 01:08:31.939
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
<i>Not the dark but the light</i>

01:08:33.100 --> 01:08:35.376
<i>Of the silvery moon</i>

01:08:35.541 --> 01:08:38.055
<i>Not the sun, but the moon</i>

01:08:38.220 --> 01:08:40.131
<i>I want to spoon</i>

01:08:40.301 --> 01:08:41.814
[IN DISTORTED VOICE]
No, you're mine.

01:08:42.020 --> 01:08:46.252
- <i>To my honey I'll croon love's tune</i>
- [IN NORMAL VOICE] <i>Croon love's tune</i>

01:08:46.861 --> 01:08:51.537
- <i>Oh, by the light of the silvery</i>
- <i>Light of the silvery</i>

01:08:52.020 --> 01:08:54.410
VELMA: <i>Moon</i>
WANDA: Oh!

01:08:54.581 --> 01:08:56.094
[GROANING]

01:09:03.501 --> 01:09:04.569
It's a dead end.

01:09:08.100 --> 01:09:10.057
I'm sorry, Daph.

01:09:10.220 --> 01:09:11.734
I really was a jerk.

01:09:11.941 --> 01:09:13.658
I'm sorry too, Fred.

01:09:13.821 --> 01:09:16.733
I never should've tried
to make you jealous.

01:09:17.621 --> 01:09:19.737
[MONSTERS ROARING]

01:09:21.180 --> 01:09:25.890
Get out of me, Wanda Grubwort.

01:09:28.821 --> 01:09:30.812
[WANDA SCREAMING]

01:09:35.060 --> 01:09:39.372
Nothing can stop me now. Come.

01:09:54.100 --> 01:09:55.978
SCOOBY:
Not so fast.

01:09:56.181 --> 01:09:57.853
What? No.

01:09:58.421 --> 01:10:01.572
Say goodbye, wicked witch.

01:10:01.781 --> 01:10:06.616
No, no. Revenge was in my grasp.

01:10:06.781 --> 01:10:09.056
And I would have gotten away
with it...

01:10:09.221 --> 01:10:13.851
...if it wasn't for you meddling kids
and your rotten dog.

01:10:14.021 --> 01:10:15.010
[GIGGLES]

01:10:15.181 --> 01:10:19.094
Oh, no. No.

01:10:20.101 --> 01:10:21.898
[SCREAMS]

01:10:22.781 --> 01:10:24.772
[MONSTERS SLITHERING]

01:10:30.261 --> 01:10:31.660
[FROGS CROAKING]

01:10:35.301 --> 01:10:37.690
Shaggy did it. Come on.

01:10:39.341 --> 01:10:41.093
VELMA:
Shaggy?

01:10:42.421 --> 01:10:44.218
Is it over?

01:10:48.141 --> 01:10:50.416
I think so, V.

01:10:52.501 --> 01:10:54.571
Those things you said to me.

01:10:56.421 --> 01:10:58.013
Did you really mean all of that?

01:10:59.101 --> 01:11:01.057
Of course I did.

01:11:01.261 --> 01:11:04.458
I've been trying to say it
ever since we got here.

01:11:06.981 --> 01:11:09.017
Just kiss her already.

01:11:09.501 --> 01:11:11.696
Oh, well, I...

01:11:11.901 --> 01:11:14.335
Shaggy, just kiss me already.

01:11:24.381 --> 01:11:25.814
SHAGGY:
Well, um...

01:11:25.981 --> 01:11:27.539
That was, uh...

01:11:28.341 --> 01:11:29.660
Yeah.

01:11:30.661 --> 01:11:33.858
You know,
I don't know too much about chemistry.

01:11:34.021 --> 01:11:35.852
I do, Shaggy.

01:11:36.061 --> 01:11:41.215
And, well, there just wasn't any.

01:11:41.381 --> 01:11:43.337
Yeah, I...

01:11:44.101 --> 01:11:48.253
You know, maybe we're just better off
being friends.

01:11:48.421 --> 01:11:50.889
You know what? Maybe we all are.

01:11:51.061 --> 01:11:52.494
Yeah.

01:11:53.461 --> 01:11:54.689
Phew.

01:11:54.861 --> 01:11:58.376
THORNY: Well, kids, with the creature
gone, we have a ton of new applications.

01:11:58.541 --> 01:12:00.213
Maybe more than we can handle.

01:12:00.821 --> 01:12:03.289
- And it's all thanks to you guys.
- Aw.

01:12:05.861 --> 01:12:08.500
Oh, that reminds me.

01:12:10.981 --> 01:12:15.293
FRED: What?
- Something to show my appreciation.

01:12:15.461 --> 01:12:18.214
- Ten thousand dollars?
- Uncle Thorny.

01:12:18.381 --> 01:12:19.939
- Oh.
- Aw.

01:12:22.141 --> 01:12:25.611
By the way, I took the liberty to set up
an appointment with my attorney...

01:12:25.781 --> 01:12:27.453
...for you to discuss incorporating.

01:12:28.101 --> 01:12:30.820
Thought that might help
with your future liability issues.

01:12:30.981 --> 01:12:32.334
- Yeah.
- Oh, man.

01:12:32.501 --> 01:12:35.254
- Shall we go play around?
SHAGGY: This is gonna be amazing, guys.

01:12:35.421 --> 01:12:37.855
- So insane.
- Hey, you guys, I've got it.

01:12:38.021 --> 01:12:40.171
We can be Mystery Incorporated.

01:12:40.341 --> 01:12:42.297
- I love it.
- I can totally dig that.

01:12:42.461 --> 01:12:43.780
Hey, Scooby, get a picture.

01:12:43.981 --> 01:12:45.255
[LAUGHS]

01:12:45.421 --> 01:12:46.774
FRED:
Everybody say, "Mystery Inc."

01:12:46.981 --> 01:12:49.290
ALL:
Mystery Inc.

01:12:49.461 --> 01:12:51.452
- Oh, my goodness.
- Guys, group hug.

01:12:51.621 --> 01:12:53.418
- Okay.
- Okay, all right.

01:12:53.581 --> 01:12:55.333
VELMA: Okay, Shaggy.
DAPHNE: Shaggy.

01:12:55.501 --> 01:12:57.776
VELMA: Shaggy.
FRED: Okay...

01:12:59.061 --> 01:13:01.291
All right. We'll celebrate.

01:13:01.501 --> 01:13:02.490
All right. Bye, guys.

01:13:02.661 --> 01:13:04.970
Not the hair, man. Not the hair.

01:13:06.101 --> 01:13:07.170
[SIGHS]

01:13:08.341 --> 01:13:09.933
[WHIMPERING]

01:13:10.101 --> 01:13:12.092
[GRUNTING]

01:13:25.221 --> 01:13:26.210
Don't worry, Scoob.

01:13:26.901 --> 01:13:30.576
No matter what happens,
I'll always be here for you.

01:13:30.781 --> 01:13:33.249
Oh, Shaggy.

01:13:45.381 --> 01:13:47.417
[SINGING]
<i>When danger used to come around</i>

01:13:47.581 --> 01:13:49.537
<i>I would fall right to the ground</i>

01:13:49.701 --> 01:13:51.851
<i>It's true</i>

01:13:53.901 --> 01:13:56.813
<i>But now that I can see your face</i>

01:13:56.981 --> 01:14:01.657
<i>Well, I can stand up to anything</i>

01:14:01.821 --> 01:14:04.494
<i>And how I cherish the times</i>

01:14:04.661 --> 01:14:09.212
<i>When the sun shines on the two of us</i>

01:14:09.621 --> 01:14:11.020
<i>But I don't mind going through</i>

01:14:11.181 --> 01:14:16.301
<i>The bad times</i>
<i>Just as long as they're with you</i>

01:14:16.861 --> 01:14:20.137
<i>Well, I can be scared with you</i>

01:14:21.221 --> 01:14:23.496
<i>I can be alone with you</i>

01:14:24.861 --> 01:14:28.979
<i>As long as I have your hand</i>
<i>To hold onto</i>

